1. Definitions

1.1 "Project" means the software mod and/or modpack identified as "Peace of Mind 21", including its source code, compiled form, configuration files, scripts, and associated assets created by the copyright holder.

1.2 "Mod" means a modification to the game Minecraft or a similar game, distributed as a separate component.

1.3 "Modpack" means a collection of one or more Mods and/or other content, packaged for combined installation or use.

1.4 "Source Code" means the human-readable form of the Project.

1.5 "Object Form" means any non-human-readable form of the Project, such as compiled code, packaged archives, or similar.

1.6 "You" (or "Your") means any individual or legal entity exercising permissions granted by this license.

1.7 "Non-Commercial Use" means any use of the Project that does not involve demanding direct payment or other direct monetary compensation specifically for access to, a copy of, or a license to the Project or any derivative work of the Project.

1.8 "Server Monetization" means generating revenue from operating a game server on which the Project is installed, including but not limited to donations, advertisements, paid cosmetic items, paid ranks, or paid access to the server itself, provided that the Project itself is not sold or marketed as a separate paid product.

1.9 "Derivative Work" means any work based upon the Project or any portion of it, including modifications, translations, or other adaptations in Source Code or Object Form.

