Subject to Your continued compliance with this license, the copyright holder hereby grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to:

2.1 Use  
(a) Download, install, and run the Project in singleplayer or multiplayer.  
(b) Use the Project in both private and public environments, including on dedicated servers.

2.2 Server Use and Monetization  
Operate servers that use the Project and engage in Server Monetization, provided that:  
(a) You do not sell, rent, or license the Project itself as a separate product; and  
(b) You do not represent the Project as Your own work or as an official version endorsed by the copyright holder.

2.3 Distribution of Unmodified Project  
Copy and redistribute the unmodified Project in Source Code or Object Form for Non-Commercial Use, including bundling it with other software, provided that:  
(a) this license text is included unmodified with every copy;  
(b) the original project name "Peace of Mind 21" and the copyright holder are clearly credited; and  
(c) You do not misrepresent Your relationship with the copyright holder.

2.4 Inclusion in Modpacks  
Include the unmodified Project in Non-Commercial Modpacks, provided that:  
(a) the Modpack is distributed free of charge, except for optional donations or general platform fees not specifically tied to the Project;  
(b) this license is included unmodified in the Modpack;  
(c) the Modpack documentation credits "Peace of Mind 21" and its copyright holder; and  
(d) You do not impose additional restrictions on the Project beyond those in this license.

For avoidance of doubt, You may operate monetized servers using a Modpack that includes the Project, subject to the conditions in Section 2.2.

2.5 Forking for Contributions and Patches  
Fork the Project's Source Code repository and create Derivative Works solely for the following purposes:  
(a) experimenting with bug fixes and improvements;  
(b) preparing patches and pull requests to be submitted back to the original Project;  
(c) creating temporary builds to test such fixes and improvements with a limited group of testers.

Any such Derivative Works may only be distributed to the extent strictly necessary to test or submit contributions to the original Project and may not be publicly released as a separate project without the copyright holder's prior written permission.

